{
  "stem": "12462.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I can show you the results in the other room, because I made a report on it to my local paper in, in the Midwest.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Why did you go to Germany during this tour of Europe?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, partly because I wanted to see what was happening in Germany beyond what I already knew from courses I took in London at the London School.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were many refugees from Hitler already that we had come across, and including a couple of members of the faculty.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I thought as a good Nordic, it would be a good thing to, [LAUGHS] to get a little experience in what life was really like in Germany.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So through a friend of mine, who was attending Oxford, we had arranged to go to the home of someone in Dusseldorf, a woman whose husband was a member of the SA, the storm troops.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was not there at the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But she entertained, or put in residence, students from England.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And instead of a student from England she got one from America, in my case.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I stayed there for a week or 10 days and traveled up to Oberhausen to the factories of one of the main [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] iron and steel works and to the Krupp works, and was shown through and given quite a bit of high-level treatment, because they somehow assumed that with my Nordic looks and all, I might be more sympathetic to them.",
      "word_count": 66
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, in fact, I was.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[GERMAN] I can speak some German, but not very well.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had three and a half years in college, but that didn't help very much.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I spent some time talking to Germans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I went out to taverns or beer halls with them.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
